    "objective": "To describe LVT pharmacokinetics in neonates",
    "covariates": "Included: WT on CL and Vd, AGE on CL",
    "observations": "Due to the mathematical description of clearance increase due to age in days, it is unsure if the clearance keeps rising in that manner after 5 days after being born. The model seems to work well for their specific population, but may not predict as well for older neonates, let alone infants and older patients. The statistical and covariate model are not fully described, which makes our description of the model in the next table only an approximation.",
    "dose": "Intravenous multiple doses in patients",
    "structure": "1 compartment with linear elimination and no absorption (IV)",
    "equations": "Vd/F=theta1*WT CL/F=theta2*WT*((AGE/5)**theta3)* (1+eta1) Cobs=Cipred *The exact covariate model was not described, we have aimed to approximate as best as possible using the available information in the paper. Furthermore, no information on the statistical model was given, other than that eta was only estimated for CL AGE is in days after being born",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.979 theta2=1.35 theta3=0.399 omega1= 0.14",
    "validation": "Yes (bootstrap of 1000) / No"
  },
